this Privacy Policy describes how Finance Flow AI ("the App", "we", "us", or "our") handles your information. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring your personal data remains secure.

Summary: Finance Flow AI is an offline-first budget tracking app. All your financial data is stored locally on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or share any personal data.

1. Information We Collect
We do not collect any personal information.

All data you enter into the App, including but not limited to:

Transaction records (income, expenses, transfers)
Budget categories and limits
Financial goals
Account information
Bill reminders
Notes and descriptions
is stored exclusively on your device using a local database. This data never leaves your device and is not accessible to us or any third party.

2. Data Storage
All your financial data is stored locally on your device using Android's built-in storage mechanisms:

Local Database: Your transactions, budgets, goals, and accounts are stored in a local database on your device.
Preferences: Your app settings and preferences are stored locally using Android DataStore.
We do not use cloud storage, remote servers, or any external databases to store your data.

3. Permissions
The App may request the following device permissions:

Camera: Used only if you choose to scan receipts or attach photos to transactions. Images are stored locally on your device.
Biometric Authentication: Used to secure app access with your fingerprint or face recognition. Biometric data is handled entirely by your device's operating system and is never accessible to the App.
Notifications: Used to send you local bill reminders and financial alerts that you configure. No push notifications are sent from external servers.
Storage: Used to export reports or backup data when you explicitly choose to do so.
Internet: The App may include internet permission for future feature updates. Currently, no user data is transmitted over the internet.
4. Data Sharing
We do not share your data with anyone.

Since all data is stored locally on your device, there is no data to share. We do not:

Sell your personal information
Share data with third parties
Use advertising networks or tracking services
Collect analytics or usage statistics
Use any third-party SDKs that collect data
5. Data Security
We take the security of your data seriously:

All data is stored locally on your device and protected by your device's built-in security.
The App supports biometric authentication (fingerprint/face) for an additional layer of security.
No data is transmitted over the internet, eliminating the risk of data interception.
6. Data Retention and Deletion
Your data remains on your device for as long as you use the App. You can delete your data at any time by:

Using the in-app delete functions for individual records
Clearing the App's data through your device settings
Uninstalling the App (this permanently removes all app data from your device)
7. Children's Privacy
The App is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect any information from children. Since the App does not collect any data at all, there is no risk of collecting children's data.

8. Third-Party Services
The App does not integrate with any third-party services that collect user data. There are no:

Analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics, Firebase Analytics)
Advertising networks
Social media integrations
Crash reporting services that collect personal data
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

